---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="How I Work — abysse8"
  description="Soft skills, measured: a 3.5-year self-audit of 10,000+ AI conversations, scored week by week and joined to the ideas I produced."
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1100px] px-6 pt-24">
    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="mb-14 max-w-[64ch]">
      <p class="font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.08em] text-accent uppercase">Soft skills, measured</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 mb-5 text-[clamp(2rem,4vw,2.8rem)] font-bold tracking-[-0.025em] text-balance">
        Most soft-skills sections are adjectives. This one is data.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-[1.05rem] text-muted">
        I exported every conversation I've had with ChatGPT since February 2023 and had an
        independent model score two things, with no cherry-picking: <strong class="font-medium text-foreground">how I
        behave</strong> — all 10,397 of my own messages, scored week by week across 161 weeks on eight
        behavioral dimensions — and <strong class="font-medium text-foreground">what I produce</strong> — 1,585 technical
        ideas mined from those same chats, each dated, attributed, and rated for quality.
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- Temperament -->
    <section class="reveal mb-20">
      <p class="font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.08em] text-accent uppercase">Temperament</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 mb-6 text-[clamp(1.4rem,3vw,1.9rem)] font-semibold tracking-[-0.02em]">Who shows up to the work.</h2>
      <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-3">
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-surface p-5">
        <div class="font-mono text-[1.7rem] font-semibold tracking-tight tabular-nums text-accent">161/178</div>
        <div class="mt-1 text-[0.9rem] font-semibold">weeks of deliberate practice</div>
        <p class="mt-1.5 text-[0.82rem] leading-normal text-muted">Active nearly every week since Feb 2023 — including all 52 weeks of 2025. Learning isn't a phase; it's a cadence.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-surface p-5">
        <div class="font-mono text-[1.7rem] font-semibold tracking-tight tabular-nums text-accent">0.14</div>
        <div class="mt-1 text-[0.9rem] font-semibold">friction, 3.5-year average</div>
        <p class="mt-1.5 text-[0.82rem] leading-normal text-muted">Conflict was my lowest-scored behavior — the single lowest dimension in a third of all weeks. I push on problems, not on people.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-surface p-5">
        <div class="font-mono text-[1.7rem] font-semibold tracking-tight tabular-nums text-accent">×2.4</div>
        <div class="mt-1 text-[0.9rem] font-semibold">growth in openness</div>
        <p class="mt-1.5 text-[0.82rem] leading-normal text-muted">My willingness to expose gaps and ask for help more than doubled (0.21 → 0.50), and honest self-review grew with it.</p>
      </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-8 max-w-[62ch] border-l-2 border-accent pl-6">
        <p class="text-[1.0rem] text-muted">
          Saying "I don't know" early is an engineering skill — it's how bugs get found before they ship.
          The judge scored my willingness to expose uncertainty and ask for help, week by week
          <span class="text-faint">(9-week smoothing)</span>:
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-6 rounded-xl border border-border bg-surface p-5">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 720 240" width="100%" role="img" aria-label="Openness in weekly AI conversations rising from 0.21 in 2023 to 0.50 in 2026 on a 0 to 1 scale" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" font-family="ui-monospace,Menlo,monospace">
<line x1="46" y1="160.0" x2="660" y2="160.0" stroke="#212127" stroke-width="1"/><text x="38" y="164.0" fill="#6b6b75" font-size="11" text-anchor="end">0.2</text><line x1="46" y1="112.0" x2="660" y2="112.0" stroke="#212127" stroke-width="1"/><text x="38" y="116.0" fill="#6b6b75" font-size="11" text-anchor="end">0.4</text><line x1="46" y1="64.0" x2="660" y2="64.0" stroke="#212127" stroke-width="1"/><text x="38" y="68.0" fill="#6b6b75" font-size="11" text-anchor="end">0.6</text><line x1="46.0" y1="16" x2="46.0" y2="208" stroke="#18181d" stroke-width="1"/><text x="46.0" y="230" fill="#6b6b75" font-size="11" text-anchor="middle">2023</text><line x1="216.6" y1="16" x2="216.6" y2="208" stroke="#18181d" stroke-width="1"/><text x="216.6" y="230" fill="#6b6b75" font-size="11" text-anchor="middle">2024</text><line x1="387.1" y1="16" x2="387.1" y2="208" stroke="#18181d" stroke-width="1"/><text x="387.1" y="230" fill="#6b6b75" font-size="11" text-anchor="middle">2025</text><line x1="557.7" y1="16" x2="557.7" y2="208" stroke="#18181d" stroke-width="1"/><text x="557.7" y="230" fill="#6b6b75" font-size="11" text-anchor="middle">2026</text>
