<circle cx="59.1" cy="156.6" r="3.5" fill="#e8a33d"/><circle cx="636.1" cy="89.0" r="3.5" fill="#e8a33d"/>
<text x="59.1" y="146.6" fill="#ededf0" font-size="12" font-weight="600" text-anchor="middle">0.21</text>
<text x="645.1" y="93.0" fill="#ededf0" font-size="12" font-weight="600">0.50</text></svg>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Output -->
    <section class="reveal mb-20">
      <p class="font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.08em] text-accent uppercase">Output</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 mb-6 text-[clamp(1.4rem,3vw,1.9rem)] font-semibold tracking-[-0.02em]">What the work produces.</h2>
      <div class="mb-8 max-w-[62ch]">
        <p class="text-[1.0rem] text-muted">
          The judge rated every mined idea for quality. The share earning a high rating has climbed
          steeply — with an honest dip in 2024:
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="mb-8 rounded-xl border border-border bg-surface p-5">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 460 210" width="100%" style="max-width:460px" role="img" aria-label="Share of ideas rated 8 or higher per year: 24 percent 2023, 16 percent 2024, 40 percent 2025, 50 percent 2026" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" font-family="ui-monospace,Menlo,monospace">
<line x1="20" y1="176" x2="450" y2="176" stroke="#212127"/><path d="M40,176 v-55 a4,4 0 0 1 4,-4 h64 a4,4 0 0 1 4,4 v55 z" fill="#e8a33d"/>
<text x="76.0" y="107.8" fill="#ededf0" font-size="14" font-weight="700" text-anchor="middle">24%</text>
<text x="76.0" y="194" fill="#9a9aa3" font-size="12" text-anchor="middle">2023</text>
<text x="76.0" y="208" fill="#6b6b75" font-size="10" text-anchor="middle">n=101</text><path d="M142,176 v-35 a4,4 0 0 1 4,-4 h64 a4,4 0 0 1 4,4 v35 z" fill="#e8a33d"/>
<text x="178.0" y="127.53333333333333" fill="#ededf0" font-size="14" font-weight="700" text-anchor="middle">16%</text>
<text x="178.0" y="194" fill="#9a9aa3" font-size="12" text-anchor="middle">2024</text>
<text x="178.0" y="208" fill="#6b6b75" font-size="10" text-anchor="middle">n=123</text><path d="M244,176 v-95 a4,4 0 0 1 4,-4 h64 a4,4 0 0 1 4,4 v95 z" fill="#e8a33d"/>
<text x="280.0" y="68.33333333333334" fill="#ededf0" font-size="14" font-weight="700" text-anchor="middle">40%</text>
<text x="280.0" y="194" fill="#9a9aa3" font-size="12" text-anchor="middle">2025</text>
<text x="280.0" y="208" fill="#6b6b75" font-size="10" text-anchor="middle">n=724</text><path d="M346,176 v-119 a4,4 0 0 1 4,-4 h64 a4,4 0 0 1 4,4 v119 z" fill="#e8a33d"/>
<text x="382.0" y="43.66666666666666" fill="#ededf0" font-size="14" font-weight="700" text-anchor="middle">50%</text>
<text x="382.0" y="194" fill="#9a9aa3" font-size="12" text-anchor="middle">2026</text>
<text x="382.0" y="208" fill="#6b6b75" font-size="10" text-anchor="middle">n=637</text></svg>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-3">
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-surface p-5">
        <div class="font-mono text-[1.7rem] font-semibold tracking-tight tabular-nums text-accent">×2.9</div>
        <div class="mt-1 text-[0.9rem] font-semibold">idea density</div>
        <p class="mt-1.5 text-[0.82rem] leading-normal text-muted">Ideas produced per message nearly tripled (0.08 → 0.23, 2023 → 2026). I extract more from every exchange than I used to.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-surface p-5">
        <div class="font-mono text-[1.7rem] font-semibold tracking-tight tabular-nums text-accent">41≈42%</div>
        <div class="mt-1 text-[0.9rem] font-semibold">weekday vs weekend</div>
        <p class="mt-1.5 text-[0.82rem] leading-normal text-muted">High-rated idea share is identical on weekdays and weekends. Curiosity doesn't clock out.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-surface p-5">
        <div class="font-mono text-[1.7rem] font-semibold tracking-tight tabular-nums text-accent">50%</div>
        <div class="mt-1 text-[0.9rem] font-semibold">of ideas are co-created</div>
        <p class="mt-1.5 text-[0.82rem] leading-normal text-muted">Half the corpus is built in genuine back-and-forth with the AI, at quality parity with either side alone. AI-augmented, not AI-dependent.</p>
      </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Killed hypothesis -->
    <section class="reveal mb-20 max-w-[64ch]">
      <p class="font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.08em] text-accent uppercase">The claim I tested and killed</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 mb-6 text-[clamp(1.4rem,3vw,1.9rem)] font-semibold tracking-[-0.02em]">Checking my own favorite story.</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-[1.0rem] text-muted">
        <p>
          I hypothesized that my emotionally intense weeks produce my best ideas — and the first
          correlation pass agreed enthusiastically. Then I controlled for a confound: busy weeks generate
          more messages, which means more ideas harvested <em>and</em> more emotional text to score.
          <strong class="font-medium text-foreground">Holding message volume fixed, the mood–quality link collapses to
          noise.</strong> The romantic version of me was a statistical artifact.
        </p>
        <p>
          One subtler signal survived, pointing the other way:
          <strong class="font-medium text-foreground">playfulness this week is the best predictor of idea quality and
          output <em>next</em> week</strong> <span class="text-faint">(r ≈ 0.27 across 109 consecutive-week pairs —
          modest, and flagged tentative since it emerged from a multi-test sweep)</span>. Lightness precedes
          fertility; anxiety predicts nothing.
        </p>
        <p class="border-l-2 border-accent pl-6 text-foreground">
          I'm keeping the dead hypothesis on this page on purpose. Testing your own favorite claim — and
          publishing the result either way — is the soft skill.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Method -->
    <section class="reveal mb-8 max-w-[64ch]">
      <p class="font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.08em] text-accent uppercase">Method, honestly</p>
      <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-[0.95rem] text-muted">
        <li class="border-l border-border pl-4">Scores come from a language-model judge reading my prompts, not a psychologist. Treat the <strong class="font-medium text-foreground">trends</strong> as signal and the second decimal as noise.</li>
        <li class="border-l border-border pl-4">Both datasets were scored by the same judge, so they could share a bias — the behavioral and output findings corroborate, they don't independently confirm.</li>
        <li class="border-l border-border pl-4">Idea ratings only span 7–10 (the inventory kept ideas already judged good), which compresses every correlation. Terse heads-down coding weeks score flat on every dimension — correctly.</li>
        <li class="border-l border-border pl-4">The raw weekly data stays private; what's published here is the aggregate story it supports.</li>
        <li class="border-l border-border pl-4">The pipeline — export → weekly segmentation → scoring → joining the two datasets → confound checks — is my own build, the same skills in the <a href="/projects/" class="text-accent hover:underline hover:underline-offset-4">projects room</a>.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>
